FT  20 MAR 93 / Judge rules on NY Post row
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A bankruptcy court judge ruled yesterday that the New York Post will remain
in the hands of Mr Abe Hirschfeld, a car parks tycoon at loggerheads with
the tabloid newspaper's staff.
Judge Francis Conrad said he would not consider offers for the newspaper
from other bidders. New York's governor Mario Cuomo, who has been trying to
organise an investor group to bid for the paper, will now have to deal
directly with Mr Hirschfeld.
Mr Steven Hoffenberg, a debt collection entrepreneur who briefly ran the
paper before a Securities and Exchange lawsuit froze his assets and
prevented him from completing the purchase, was barred from interfering with
the sale to Mr Hirschfeld.
