FT  20 MAR 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: Week Ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wellcome, the UK pharmaceuticals group, reports half-year results on
Thursday with analysts forecasting pre-tax profits of between Pounds 295m
and Pounds 325m against Pounds 244m a year earlier on sales of about Pounds
1bn.
Retrovir, the HIV-treatment, is expected to generate between Pounds 120m and
Pounds 140m, while estimates for sales of Zovirax, the herpes and chickenpox
medicine, range from Pounds 345m to Pounds 385m.
Bowater, the packaging and industrial films group, announces its 1992
results on Tuesday. It released estimated results, showing an unaudited
pre-tax profit of Pounds 147m, a 48.5 per cent increase on 1991, last month
when it announced the Dollars 434m acquisition of Specialty Coatings
international, the US coatings company.
Full-year results on Tuesday from Invergordon Distillers, the independent
Scotch whisky producer, are likely to reflect the increased pressure on
margins in the bulk whisky market. After five years of strong growth,
pre-tax profits are expected to be virtually flat at Pounds 32.4m against
Pounds 32.2m in 1991.
