FT  20 MAR 93 / New bomb blast in Calcutta
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SHIRAZ SIDHVA
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
At least one person was killed and 11 injured when a bomb exploded at
Calcutta's crowded Sealdah station last night, writes Shiraz Sidhva in New
Delhi. The explosives were reported to have been in a suitcase.
The explosion was the second in Calcutta in less than four days, after a
bomb blast in the busy Bowbazar area late on Tuesday night left 86 dead and
over 70 injured.
Police say that the blasts in Calcutta are not linked to the series of bomb
attacks which rocked Bombay last Friday, leaving over 250 dead.
