Mr Attilio Bastianini, one of three deputy leaders of Italy's small Liberal
Party, was arrested by Milan magistrates on corruption charges yesterday,
writes Robert Graham in Rome.
The arrest of Mr Bastianini, a 50-year-old lecturer at Turin's prestigous
