FT  19 MAR 93 / World News in Brief: Canadian bank buys bulk of Royal
Trustco
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Royal Bank of Canada is to buy the bulk of the operations of Royal Trustco,
Canada's second-biggest trust company, for CDollars 1.65bn (USDollars
1.3bn). The acquisition will boost Royal Bank's assets by about CDollars
14bn, or 10 per cent, and give it access to a variety of fiduciary and
investment management services. Royal Trustco suffered large losses on
businesses it acquired during the 1980s in Europe and the US, as well as
losses in its core Canadian mortgage market.
